Kannywood actress, Rahama Sadau on Monday was recognized by the Women Illuminated Film Festival Parallel to United Nations as a 'shining light'. The actress who was in New York shared photos from the event on her social media page. She captioned it, "I've been honoured last night. I'm so privileged, delighted and very very PROUD to share the beautiful evening with so many incredibly amazing women.There are moments in life when you stop and ask yourself, how did I even get here? Well this is definitely one of those moments I would cherish forever.